node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Women In Medicine on August 24, 2021 tagging @womeninmedicine. May be an image of text.

node.text:
KNOW 👏🏼 YOUR 👏🏽 WORTH 👏🏾

Found this posted on another medical group site and instantly felt a jab in the heart. 💔 We work SO hard, we accommodate for so much, and we are quite often under appreciated. But we get up and do it all again, day after day. 

One of my first Attending salary offers (from a place I was super excited about btw) was so low I actually cried. I had spent 13 years preparing for this moment and was so disheartened and slightly panicking bc I knew I had loan repayments coming on quick that I wouldn’t be able to afford. I got a locum job that turned out to be fantastic and ultimately found my home at an Allergy clinic I love. Took a minute, but please please know your worth! Negotiate, say NO when you have to, take care of yourself! 

(Btw nothing wrong with that salary at all, just unrealistic expectations for the degrees preferred)! 

We are #womeninmedicine 
@womeninmedicine 

📸 PSG Facebook group

May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'AlwaysAshley @AshleyFrankly Prior authorizations be ike My doctor: You need this medicine. Dr to pharmacy: She needs this medicine. Pharmacy to insurance: Her doctor says she needs this medicine. Insurance: Does she though? Let's ask her doctor.'.

node.text:
What really got me was the peer-to-peer with a doc who had never heard of the med I was prescribing..and after explaining it they said “ohh that sounds like it will really work” - I mean, yea that’s why I prescribed it! 🤦🏻‍♀️ 

Can anyone relate??

So frustrating when our attempt at good/proper healthcare is put through so many limiting steps! 

We are proud, strong yet sometimes quite frustrated #womeninmedicine @womeninmedicine

node.text:
Come on Barbie, let’s go party...🩺💉🩸🦠

And by that we mean endless hours over the past 1.5 years (feels like eternity) learning about, caring for, and attempting to prevent all things COVID. 

Honored to have so many of our #womeninmedicine transformed into @barbie dolls. We know this does not represent *all* types of women in medicine, but an incredible step in the right direction and tremendously encouraging role models for kids (& adults) everywhere! 

Proud #womeninmedicine 
#womenempowerment #womeninstem #healthcareheroes 

@womeninmedicine 
@barbie @mattel
